# Basic Training — Lesson Style Template

When editing or adding lessons in `apps/landing/src/data/basicTraining.ts`, follow this style (established from the HUD lesson).

## Format

- **No `---` dashes** between sections.
- **Section headers:** Use `[SECTION]Title[/SECTION]` — clear, sentence case, not ALL CAPS.
- **Checklists:** Use `[CHECKLIST]` ... `[END_CHECKLIST]` for steps.
- **Checkpoint** at the end of every lesson.
- **Session-only notes** at end when relevant: "Changes apply to this session only. For permanent defaults: ..."

## Section titles

Use clear, readable titles:
- Good: "What the HUD is", "Key elements", "Setup via MFD", "Flight settings"
- Avoid: "WHAT THE HUD IS", "SETUP — VIA MFD"

## Structure

1. Brief intro (1–2 sentences)
2. [SECTION] blocks for logical groupings
3. [CHECKLIST] where applicable
4. Checkpoint

## Renderer

The BasicTraining component parses `[SECTION]` and renders them as styled headings (accent color, uppercase, tracked). No code changes needed — just use the tags in the lesson text.
